## 2. Product Evolution — Three Phases

**Phase 1-2: Cactus as Middleware**
WMS platforms (Warehance, etc.) call the Cactus Rating API.
Cactus calls carriers, applies markup, returns rates.
WMS handles the display and selection UI.
Cactus handles billing, invoicing, reconciliation.

**Phase 3: Cactus as Full OS**
Cactus builds its own WMS — end-to-end ownership.
No dependency on third-party WMS platforms.
Full warehouse management: aisles, bins, pick/pack, inventory.
Cactus owns the complete logistics stack.

**The strategic advantage of this sequence:**
By the time Cactus builds its own WMS, the Shadow Ledger will
have accumulated millions of shipments worth of intelligence
from third-party WMS integrations. The Cactus WMS launches
with AI capabilities that took years to build — not months.

