## 5. Carrier Account Architecture

### The Two Modes

**`lassoed_carrier_account`**
WMS integrated. Full label-print visibility. shipment_ledger
row created at print time. Full reconciliation available.
Invoice matching: tracking_number → shipment_ledger → org_id

**`dark_carrier_account`**
Client entered Cactus credentials into their own platform.
Zero visibility at label print. Invoice-only billing.
Invoice matching: ship_from_address_normalized → locations

### The is_cactus_account Flag
- TRUE (default): Cactus earns margin. Apply markup.
- FALSE: Pass-through. No owned revenue. Skip markup.

### Carrier Account Hierarchy
```
organizations
    └── org_carrier_accounts
            ├── markup_percentage  ← applied to BOTH API rates and rate cards
            ├── use_rate_card      ← master switch: API vs rate card pricing
            ├── dispute_threshold
            ├── carrier_account_mode
            ├── is_cactus_account
            └── rate_cards (active when use_rate_card = TRUE)
                    ├── nickname       ← human-readable label in The Alamo
                    ├── service_level  ← e.g. UPS_GROUND, GROUND_ADVANTAGE
                    ├── base_rate      ← always pre-markup, never includes markup
                    ├── effective_date ← rate card not used until this date
                    └── deprecated_date ← rate card expires on this date
```

### All carrier accounts are Cactus/Buku master accounts.
No per-org carrier credentials to store.

### use_rate_card Flag (on org_carrier_accounts)
FALSE (default): Rating engine calls carrier API. Markup applied on top.
TRUE: Rating engine uses rate cards instead of carrier API.
  - Rate card stores BASE rate only — never includes markup
  - Markup percentage on carrier account applied on top of rate card
  - Single-Ceiling applied once to (rate_card_base × (1 + markup))
  - If no rate card exists for a service level → no rate returned
  - is_active is NOT stored on rate_cards — it is computed (see Rate Card Active State below)
  - Future: USPS may have zone/weight tiered rate cards (Phase 3)

### Rate Card Rating Flow
IF use_rate_card = TRUE:
  Look up rate card for carrier_account + service_level where:
    effective_date <= CURRENT_DATE
    deprecated_date IS NULL OR deprecated_date > CURRENT_DATE
  ORDER BY effective_date DESC LIMIT 1
  IF found → base_rate × (1 + markup) → Single-Ceiling → return rate
  IF not found → exclude this service level (no rate returned)
IF use_rate_card = FALSE:
  Call carrier API → apply markup → Single-Ceiling → return rate

### Rate Card Active State — Computed, Never Stored
is_active is NOT a stored field on rate_cards.
Computed at read time from three conditions (AND logic):
  1. org_carrier_accounts.use_rate_card = TRUE
  2. rate_cards.effective_date <= CURRENT_DATE
  3. rate_cards.deprecated_date IS NULL
     OR rate_cards.deprecated_date > CURRENT_DATE
All three must be TRUE for a rate card to be active.
The Alamo UI displays computed active state — never a stored boolean.

### Rate Card Date Fields
created_at:       auto-populated at upload — audit trail only
effective_date:   admin-set — rate card not used until this date
deprecated_date:  admin-set — rate card expires on this date

Future-dating: upload new rates in advance, they go live automatically.
Superseding: new effective_date > old → new card wins automatically.

