## 7. Invoice Pipeline — The Billing Brain

### Variance Calculation Rule — Non-Negotiable
variance_amount = carrier_charge - raw_carrier_cost
Both values are pre-markup carrier costs — apples to apples.
NEVER compare carrier_charge to final_billed_rate.
The markup difference would create false variance on every shipment.
is_adjustment_only=TRUE skips variance calc (no original quote exists).

### Full Flow (v1.6.0 — 8 stages)
See master briefing Section 8 for canonical stage-by-stage definitions.

```
STAGE 1: INGESTION
  Upload carrier CSV/XLSX in The Alamo, file stored in Supabase Storage

STAGE 2: PARSING
  AI normalization OR rule-based parser (per format)
  service_level from Charge Description (primary FRT row)
  is_adjustment_only flagged when only adjustment FRT rows exist

STAGE 3: MATCHING (no markup applied at this stage)
  Lassoed: tracking_number → shipment_ledger → org_id
    Enrich date_shipped from shipment_events.LABEL_CREATED
    Variance check (skip if is_adjustment_only)
  Dark: address_sender_normalized → locations → org_id

STAGE 4: DISPUTE RESOLUTION
  Admin reviews HELD lines, assigns org or approves variance

STAGE 5: BILLING CALCULATION (NEW SEPARATE STAGE)
  Apply markup per markup_type, write final_billed_rate
  Write markup context: markup_type_applied, markup_value_applied, markup_source

STAGE 6: INVOICE GENERATION
  Group by org, create cactus_invoices + junction rows

STAGE 7: DELIVERY TO PORTAL
  PDF summary + 85-column CSV detail format

STAGE 8: PAYMENT
  Stripe auto-pull on due_date, shipment_ledger immutable
```

### Address Normalization Format
`"1234 MAIN ST, PHOENIX, AZ, 85001, US"`
Uppercase. Abbreviated street type. State abbreviation.

