## 10b. User Roles & Notification Architecture

### Portal Role Enum
ADMIN: full portal access + user management. Notifications ON.
FINANCE: full portal access. Notifications ON.
STANDARD: all except sub-client billing. Notifications OFF.
Stored on org_users.role as portal_role_enum.
Seeded to STANDARD by default on new user creation.

### Notification Types
METER_RELOAD | INVOICE_READY | TRACKING_STATUS_ALERTS | PAYMENT_FAILED
Stored in notification_preferences table.
One row per user per org per type.
Seeded by trigger on org_users insert based on role.
User-adjustable in Cactus Portal settings.

### Tracking Alert Categories (TRACKING_STATUS_ALERTS)
NO_MOVEMENT: LABEL_CREATED > threshold days, no subsequent scan
STALE_IN_TRANSIT: IN_TRANSIT/PICKED_UP > threshold days, no scan
DAMAGED: event_type = DAMAGED
UNDELIVERABLE: DELIVERY_ATTEMPTED with no DELIVERED follow-up
RETURNED_TO_SENDER: event_type = RETURNED_TO_SENDER
Digest: daily at 7:00am, scans 14 days, totals per category only
Threshold: organizations.tracking_alert_threshold_days (default 3)
Scale: direct query → shipment_alert_cache → read replica

### Email Delivery
Provider: Resend (native Next.js SDK)
Templates: React Email — one component per notification type
Invoice email: HTML summary in body, portal link for file downloads
No PDF/CSV attachments — spam filter deliverability.

### Non-Negotiable Rules
- Never block org_users insert if preference seeding fails
- Trigger must have EXCEPTION WHEN OTHERS handler
- notification_type_enum is the source of truth for valid types
- New notification types require enum migration + template build
- STANDARD role never receives notifications unless user opts in
- Alamo auth model is separate from Cactus Portal auth model

