## 10c. Page Standards — Search, Filter, Export

### Required on all list and report pages
Every page that displays a list of records must include at the top
of the page body, above all table/list content:

1. SEARCH INPUT
   - Searches tracking numbers and unique identifiers
   - Also searches relevant text fields (file names, org names, etc.)

2. FILTER COMPONENTS
   - Date range: FROM and TO date inputs (label style: 11px uppercase muted)
   - Carrier type: dropdown of carrier_code_enum values
   - Invoice/record status: dropdown of relevant status enum
   - Org: dropdown when cross-org data is displayed

3. EXPORT CSV BUTTON
   - Exports the current filtered dataset
   - Applies same display rules as the page (lassoed vs dark invoice rules)
   - Available on all report and invoice pages

### Layout rule
Search + filters + export live in a single bar at the top of the
page body. All filtering is client-side state — no full page reloads.
These are client components. The parent page (server component) passes
the full dataset as a prop; the filter component handles display logic.

### Non-negotiable
- Never build a list/report page without search and filter
- Export CSV is always present on invoice and report pages
- FROM/TO date labels use 11px uppercase muted style (Alamo standard)

### CSV Format Conventions (locked v1.6.0)

Client-facing CSV exports use the 85-column "detail format":

- Tracking numbers: tab-prefixed to prevent Excel scientific notation
- Dates: ISO format YYYY-MM-DD
- Currency: plain decimal, 2 places, no currency symbol
- Empty cells: literally empty (never "NULL", never 0 for missing numerics)
- CSV dialect: RFC 4180, CRLF line endings, UTF-8 with BOM
- Filename: {org-slug}-cactus-invoice-{week-end-date}.csv
- No metadata header rows — column headers row 1, data row 2 onward
- Per-charge billed values computed at read time from raw + markup context
- Footnote on CSV: "Shipment Total is authoritative. Line items may reflect fractional-cent display rounding."

Internal Alamo CSV exports (filter/list exports) follow the same
conventions except they MAY include Cactus-internal columns
(carrier_charge, variance, markup context) since those views are admin-only.

