## 11. Coding Philosophy

- WHY comments on every non-obvious block
- Rate card failure never halts label production
- Idempotency keys on all label purchases and meter reloads
- Async Shadow Ledger writes — never block rating response
- Graceful carrier API error handling — never fail entire response
- Performance: Rating < 500ms, Label < 2000ms, Dashboard < 1s

---

## 12. Security Standards
- API keys in `.env` only — never hardcoded
- `.env` in `.gitignore` — never committed
- Payment tokens only — raw card data never in Cactus
- Service role key — backend only, never in browser
- All timestamps: `TIMESTAMPTZ`

