--cactus-sand:         #F0EEE9  page background
--cactus-border:       #DDD8D0  all borders
--cactus-border-mid:   #CCC8C0  form input borders
--cactus-border-bloom: #F0A8C8  bloom-state borders

### Typography Scale
Display:    20-24px / weight 500 / ink / tracking -0.02em
Body:       13px / weight 400 / ink
Muted:      13px / weight 400 / muted
Label:      11px / weight 500 / muted / tracking 0.03em
Nav label:  10px / weight 500 / hint / tracking 0.07em / uppercase
Mono:       12px / SF Mono or Fira Code / forest
            (all tracking numbers, IDs, account numbers)
Form input: 13px / weight 500 / ink

### Spacing Scale
Page padding:      20px 24px
Card header:       12px 16px
Card body:         14px 16px
Table cell:        10px 16px
Stat card:         14px 16px
Form row gap:      12px
Nav item:          6px 8px
Nav section:       12px 8px 4px

### Border Radius Scale
Form inputs:       6px
Badges:            20px (full pill)
Stat cards:        8px
Cards:             10px
Shell / modals:    12px

### Non-Negotiable Rules
- Border: always 0.5px — never 1px, never 2px
- No shadows of any kind
- No gradients of any kind
- No pure black — use ink (#0D1210)
- Form inputs: font-weight 500
- Active nav: forest green only
- Active disputes nav: bloom
- Focus ring: 0 0 0 3px rgba(45,90,39,0.10)
- Mono font for ALL tracking numbers and IDs
- Badges: always pill shape, never square
- Variance columns: bloom color when positive (overcharge)
- Cactus Portal never shows carrier_charge on lassoed account lines
- locations.name is the human-friendly location label
  Use short names: "Phoenix WH", "Tempe FC", "SLC Returns"

### Semantic Color Usage

Default state — everything is quiet:
  Text:              ink #0D1210
  Borders:           #DDD8D0
  Backgrounds:       canvas #F8F6F2
  Badges:            subtle tint, never loud

Approved / confirmed:
  Badge text:        forest #2D5A27
  Badge bg:          mint #EEF4EB
  No row highlighting — approved is the default expected state

Lassoed / dark account mode:
  Badge text:        slate #3D4744
  Badge bg:          #E8ECEB
  No row highlighting

Held / dispute — minor variance:
  Badge only:        bloom text #D81B7A on bloom-bg #FCE4F0
  Row:               no fill — badge carries the signal
  Variance text:     bloom #D81B7A on the variance column only

Held / dispute — major variance (e.g. >$10):
  Row left border:   2px solid #D81B7A (the ONLY moment bloom goes structural)
  Badge:             bloom as above
  Variance text:     bloom

Alert banners:
  Minor:             muted border + canvas bg + bloom text
  Major:             bloom-bg #FCE4F0 + bloom-border #F48CBB

Savings highlights (Portal):
  Number text only:  amber #D97706
  No fills

### The Rule in Plain English
Color lives in text and badges first.
It moves to borders only when action is truly required.
The screen should feel calm until something genuinely needs you.

### The Two Portal Expressions
The Alamo (internal):
  Primary CTA:     forest #2D5A27
  Data density:    Stripe-level
  Spacing:         compact

Cactus Portal (client-facing):
  Primary CTA:     amber #D97706
  Data density:    Apple-level restraint
  Spacing:         generous, more breathing room